<section class="py-24 md:py-36 bg-warm-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Section header -->
      <div class="max-w-2xl reveal">
        <p class="text-giving font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase">
          The first principle
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-text-deep leading-[1.05]">
          Why giving comes before saving.
        </h2>
      </div>

      <!-- Body content: editorial two-column -->
      <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-12">
        <div class="md:col-span-6 space-y-6 text-lg text-text-body leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <p>
            Most financial advice says "pay yourself first." Put money into savings before you spend it. Build your wealth. Prioritize your future.
          </p>
          <p>
            It's not bad advice. But it's not our advice.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="md:col-span-5 md:col-start-8 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <!-- Pull quote -->
          <div class="p-8 bg-giving/5 rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-giving">
            <p class="font-quote text-2xl text-giving italic leading-snug">
              "Give first. Save second. Spend what's left."
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Continuation -->
      <div class="mt-16 max-w-2xl space-y-6 text-lg text-text-body leading-relaxed reveal">
        <p>
          The order reveals your priorities.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Bible describes a principle called "firstfruits" (Proverbs 3:9) &mdash; give from the first of what you receive, not from what's left over. It's about generosity as a posture, giving back to God before you do anything else.
        </p>
        <p>
          When giving comes first, everything else falls into perspective. Saving becomes provision, not hoarding. Spending becomes enjoyment, not guilt.
        </p>
        <p>
          Storehouse is built around this order. Your giving priorities sit at the top. Your Safe to Spend number reflects what's left after generosity is handled.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
